  "text": "The attention module in general can be considered as a search mechanism, e.g. in the original encoder-decoder architecture the basic attention module finds the most relevant input words to make the prediction. In multi-modal NMT [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] an extra attention module is added to the basic one in order to search the image input to find the most relevant image segments. In our case we have a similar additional attention module which searches the morphology table.",
